<br>
How about finding some books on debate theory, or some books on what reason/logic/scientific method  constitute?<br>
<br>
I am asking, in all sincerity, that you do that, because otherwise, you will have a hard time debating on this board, if you don't understand the difference, if you don't understand how the terms work. It confuses your audience, and it loses the impact of any point you try to make when you interchange non-interchangeable points.<br>
<br>
Reason and faith are not the same. They are two points on different charts. They are used to measure different things. Your feelings, someone else's feelings, have nothing to do with reason.<br>
<br>
Feelings can be important. However, they are a different measure of the world than reason is, for the main reason that they cannot be experienced the same way by everyone.<br>
<br>
If feelings were an accurate barometer of truth, why isn't everyone on the planet the same religion? Why don't people all find the same type of person attractive? I could go on for days to illustrate the difference.<br>
<br>
It all goes back to the right tools for the job. And in this instance, your feelings on an episode that happened 500+ years ago are your feelings, and your feelings only. Not a point on the trip to reason.<br>
<br>
Jessica <br>
