No I did not.  Reality exists.  It is an objective reality.  We view it subjectively.  That reality will continue to exist independantly no matter what we believe or if we ever prove any of it.  Truth cannot be felt.  Feelings are felt.  Emotions are felt.  Sensations are felt.  None of this relates to fact.  Facts by virtue of being truth can be tested and proven to be facts.  I made an analogy that 150,000,000 people bought lottery tickets, and one got to be a winner.  You can have 150,000,000 feelings, one may ACCIDENTALLY endorse a fact, that does not make it a proof for that fact.  It just means you had a lucky guess, just like the jerk who won my money 2 weeks ago.  Heck, every one could endorse a fact, that still doesn't make it an accurate test, it only makes you one lucky guesser.<br>
<br>
Truth can be proven.  We do not currently (as someone already pointed out) have the ability to prove everything, but our knowledge and ability improves every day.  <br>
